<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Surstylus bifid, the upper lobe with about 5 thin, peg-like prensisetae and 1 fine seta, the below one with 1 thin, peg-like prensiseta and 2 fine setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7A, B</figureCitation>
); gonopods undeveloped (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂, ♀) 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3A</figureCitation>
): Frons yellowish brown. Pedicel and first flagellomere maple. Facial carina yellowish, short, 1/3 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3C, E</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum yellowish. Acrostichal setulae in ca 8 regular rows. Wings hyaline.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3C, E</figureCitation>
): Tergites and sternites yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium with ca 14 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium glabrous (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
). Paramere slender and curved apically, with 3 sensillae subbasally (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Female terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7E</figureCitation>
): Oviscapt with 2 long subapical trichoid ovisensilla, 17 peg-like ovisensilla on each side on ventral margins and 5 trichoid ovisensilla on dorsal.
</paragraph>
